    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-08T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-08T02:00:00-05:00" n="141"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/9–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Greek Government in Exile</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 8, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 8—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Greek 294. The Greek Government officially left Cairo for Italy yesterday, the
                    Prime Minister and most of the Cabinet leaving by air with the rest to follow in
                    next few days by sea accompanied by subordinate personnel. The Crown Prince
                        Regent<note n="17" xml:id="d141fn17">Prince Paul.</note> expects to go next
                    week (Embassy’s 289, September 5<note n="18" xml:id="d141fn18">Not
                        printed.</note>).</p>
                <p>Before departure the Government issued a declaration which was broadcast to the
                    Greek people and of which a summary is contained in my immediately following
                        telegram.<note n="19" xml:id="d141fn19">Telegram Greek Series No. 295,
                        September 8, 11 a.m., not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
